[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "e6e1ad8867c787422b896d8a20f35b3894b5522ca675b2e80d4ae0fb10f80f32"]
[Category "Defense"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "defense/defensive_signals"]
[Student "W"]
{You are South. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \H4, North takes the \HA and returns the \H3. You ruff and then play what??? 

Play a low \C.

Partner played the \H3, a low card, for you to ruff. That means his re-entry, if he has one, is in the lower-ranking suit.

Partner takes the \CA and gives you a second \H ruff.}
[Play "W"]H4

